.Sh NAME
.Nm kiesel
.Nd A JavaScript engine written in Zig
.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl c , \-command Ar command
.Op Fl d , \-debug
.Op Fl \-disable-gc
.Op Fl m , \-module
.Op Fl \-print-ast
.Op Fl \-print-bytecode
.Op Fl \-print-gc-warnings
.Op Fl \-print-promise-rejection-warnings
.Op Fl p , \-print-result
.Op Fl v , \-version
.Op Fl h , \-help
.Op file
.
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a JavaScript engine written from scratch with the eventual goal of full
support for the latest ECMAScript standard.
.Pp
The command line options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl c , \-command Ar command
Runs
.Ar command
instead of reading from a file.
.It Fl d , \-debug
Enables the debug mode, offering a more detailed output.
.It Fl \-disable-gc
Disables the garbage collection, resulting in memory leaks.
.It Fl m , \-module
Runs the code as a module instead of a script.
.It Fl \-print-ast
Prints the parsed AST for
.Ar file
or every statement in the interactive input.
Continues with normal execution afterwards.
.It Fl \-print-bytecode
Prints the generated bytecode for
.Ar file
or every statement in the interactive input.
Continues with normal execution afterwards.
.It Fl \-print-gc-warnings
Prints the warnings from the garbage collector, e.g. out-of-memory situations.
.It Fl \-print-promise-rejection-warnings
Prints promise rejection warnings.
.It Fl p , \-print-result
Prints the evaluated result for
.Ar file
at the end of its execution.
This behavior is default when running in interactive mode.
.It Fl v , \-version
Prints the version and exits.
.It Fl h , \-help
Prints a help text and exits.
.El
.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Place the following in a file named
.Ql script.js :
.Bd -literal -offset indent
const words = [ "meow :3", "awawawa", "uwu" ];
for (let i = 0; i < words.length: i++) {
	console.log(words[i]);
}
.Ed
.Pp
Executing the following command:
.Dl kiesel script.js
will result in:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
meow :3
awawawa
uwu
.Ed
.
